1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,966
[electro pop music playing]

2
00:00:11,803 --> 00:00:13,888
[McEnroe] For as long
as Devi could remember,

3
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:17,851
Valentine's Day had been nothing
but a humbling annual reminder

4
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:20,061
that she was a stone-cold loser.

5
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:22,522
You will always be my Valentine, kanna.

6
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,065
[kisses]

7
00:00:26,484 --> 00:00:28,486
[McEnroe] As far as she was concerned,

8
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,488
this holiday sucked a fat one.

9
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,574
[music continues]

10
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:39,205
Whoops, sorry, little boy.
I'm supposed to be next door.

11
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:43,376
[McEnroe] But today, Devi had a boyfriend,

12
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:46,296
and Valentine's Day
was gonna frickin' rule.

13
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:47,756
-Happy Valentine's Day.
-[Devi] Hey.

14
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:50,008
I've got a really romantic date
planned for us tonight.

15
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,093
-[Devi] Ooh.
-I Febrezed my futon and everything.

16
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:53,011
[both chuckle]

17
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:56,765
[McEnroe] Put that in your vape pen
and vape it, loser single girls.

18
00:00:57,265 --> 00:01:00,518
All right. Well, I gotta grab some things
before class, but I'll see you later.

19
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:01,436
[Devi] Okay.

20
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:06,357
-[McEnroe] Nothing was gonna ruin today.
-[sighs]

21
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:08,234
-Hey, what's up?
-Yo, what up, dude?

22
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:12,030
[McEnroe] Not even the fear that Devi
may have inadvertently rekindled something

23
00:01:12,113 --> 00:01:14,991
between Paxton and his smoking hot ex.

24
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,910
-Oh, Paxton, wait. Guess what?
-Yep.

25
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:18,912
You're my perfect match.

26
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:22,499
What are you talking about?
What is that? Oh!

27
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:23,458
Happy Valentine's.

28
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,293
Here's your results
from the student council's

29
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:27,462
compatibility quiz
you took yesterday at lunch.

30
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:30,965
["Run It Up Pt. II" by Spilt Milk playing]

31
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:33,676
[McEnroe] Oh God.

32
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,721
Maybe there's another Eric Perkins
at this school.

33
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,393
-[boy] No way, man.
-[girl] Walk much?

34
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:43,770
What?

35
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,981
♪ Run it up, run it up
Run it up, run it up ♪

36
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:48,566
♪ Run it up, run it up, run it ♪

37
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:49,859
♪ Run it up, run it up ♪

38
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,861
[Devi] Valentine's Day sucks!

39
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:55,406
I just don't get how I, a person
who's dating the hottest boy in school,

40
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,367
is most compatible with Eric.

41
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:59,536
Are you more mad that you got Eric,

42
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:01,371
or that Haley got Paxton?

43
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,372
[sighs]

44
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:04,332
I'm happy that they're friends again.

45
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:06,626
I just wish
they weren't such good friends.

46
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:10,713
You don't have to worry about Haley.
Paxton is super into you.

47
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:14,509
I know, but he and Haley
have known each other forever,

48
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:15,718
and they have had sex.

49
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,720
And now I'm picturing them having sex and…

50
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:20,932
Oh my God, I realized why the computer
said they were a perfect match.

51
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:22,767
Don't read into it that much.

52
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:26,479
It's just a dumb quiz made
by dumb teenagers in a dumb school.

53
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:27,397
Hey, guys.

54
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:30,108
[inhales deeply] Hi, Aneesa.

55
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:34,571
[McEnroe] This awkward hello is courtesy
of the following interaction

56
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:36,114
that has yet to be discussed.

57
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:43,079
Um, did you just call this quiz dumb?

58
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:46,249
It was actually developed
by Nobel prize-winning scientists at MIT.

59
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:48,334
Its accuracy is undisputed.

60
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:50,211
So, educate yourselves.

61
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:52,463
Sorry, Jonah.

62
00:02:56,342 --> 00:03:00,180
I can't believe I got Gears Brosnan.
I didn't even know he filled out a quiz.

63
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:02,390
-Who'd you guys get?
-I got Trent.

64
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:03,600
Yeah, I got Ben.

65
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:06,352
Oh wow, Ben. That's so cool

66
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:09,063
since he's your boyfriend and all.

67
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:12,150
Hey, Fab, do you feel weird today?

68
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,903
Why? Do I seem weird? Does it seem
like something weird happened?

69
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:17,906
No, I was just wondering
'cause, you know, it's Valentine's Day,

70
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,157
and you must miss Eve.

71
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,451
Oh. Um… [sighs]

72
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:24,537
Yeah, yeah, that's-- I do. I miss her.

73
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,998
Speaking of relationships,

74
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:30,710
I don't think all the couples here
are gonna make it through Valentine's.

75
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:31,878
-What?
-Why do you say that?

76
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:34,005
Because I need to dump Trent.

77
00:03:34,088 --> 00:03:36,090
Wait, I thought things were going well.

78
00:03:36,174 --> 00:03:37,884
I mean, it's been fun.

79
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,385
He's just not very deep.

80
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:40,970
Like, I'm a second away

81
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:45,016
from bursting into either song or tears
at every moment of the day.

82
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:49,270
Shouldn't I be with another artist
or at least another Sagittarius?

83
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:51,314
Got you, babe.

84
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:52,440
Oh, hey.

85
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,691
Yeah, I got you too.

86
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:56,444
[inhales deeply] Wow,
those MIT guys are good.

87
00:03:57,779 --> 00:03:58,613
I guess.

88
00:03:58,696 --> 00:04:03,201
But doesn't this quiz feel kind of creepy?
Like, real 1984 vibes.

89
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,786
The Taylor Swift album?

90
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:06,663
[snorts] No, Aneesa.

91
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,289
The book by George Orwell.

92
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:11,542
God, I've gotta get you
a little library card, huh?

93
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:15,755
I'd argue that 1989
has more literary relevance

94
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:17,632
than anything George Orwell ever wrote.

95
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,805
Is that true? I only listen to podcasts.

96
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:28,434
Dr. Vishwakumar,
your next patient is here.

97
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:30,353
[chuckling]

98
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:33,273
Hi. Rhyah, what brings you in today?

99
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:35,650
Oh, I just wanted to say hi.

100
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,777
Also, I have this tiny burning rash
going up my arm,

101
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:39,737
but I mostly just wanted to say hi.

102
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,114
Okay, let me take a look.

103
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:43,032
-[Rhyah] Okay.
-How are things with you?

104
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,535
-I'm good. How are you doing?
-Good. Good, good.

105
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,203
-Itchy?
-Yeah.

106
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,080
-[Nalini] Kind of flaky?
-Little bit.

107
00:04:49,163 --> 00:04:50,665
Mmm. Looks like tinea corporis.

108
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:53,167
-Oh, what's that?
-It's basically athlete's foot.

109
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:55,503
Or in this case,
we can call it athlete's forearm.

110
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:59,215
[gasps] See, I knew my yoga studio
wasn't washing their mats properly.

111
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,342
I stayed late one time
and watched them flip 'em over.

112
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,511
Don't worry about it.
It's actually fairly common.

113
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:05,972
I'm just gonna write you a prescription
for anti-fungal cream.

114
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:07,515
It should clear up in a few weeks.

115
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:10,435
Fungal infection on Valentine's Day.
[chuckling] Very sexy.

116
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:11,936
Do you have any plans tonight?

117
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:15,565
[McEnroe] Nalini had completely forgotten
about Valentine's Day.

118
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:18,318
She had always considered it
a stupid holiday.

119
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:21,112
But now with Mohan gone,
it felt different.

120
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:22,071
No.

121
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,199
Mohan, no.

122
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:29,245
We agreed last year
no Valentine's Day gifts.

123
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:31,664
This is different. You'll like it.

124
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:35,001
I spent hardly any money.

125
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:37,086
[sentimental music playing]

126
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:46,929
You got me a bobblehead of you?

127
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,139
Yeah.

128
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:51,225
Now you can knock me around
when I'm being hardheaded.

129
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:54,937
Did you give yourself a stronger jaw?

130
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:56,689
Well…

131
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:57,732
Maybe.

132
00:05:58,274 --> 00:06:00,193
[Nalini chuckles]

133
00:06:06,282 --> 00:06:07,909
[sighs] Nope.

134
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,453
No Valentine's Day plans

135
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:13,373
other than tending to the many
demanding people in my household

136
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:15,249
who drain me of my money and energy.

137
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,418
Well, you should still celebrate.

138
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:22,340
Hey, you need to carve out
some fun time for you.

139
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:23,341
Every day.

140
00:06:24,425 --> 00:06:27,470
I already do that for six hours
every night when I'm asleep.

141
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:30,056
That's not what I mean.

142
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:33,434
What are you doing tomorrow night?
Let's have a gals hang.

143
00:06:34,352 --> 00:06:35,603
Oh. Uh…

144
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:37,814
I don't think I can.

145
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:39,023
Just really busy.

146
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:39,941
Sorry.

147
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:41,943
Okay, no worries.

148
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:44,779
But I'm gonna leave you my number
just in case you change your mind.

149
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:46,614
-[Tracey] Dr. Vishwakumar.
-[Nalini] Mm-hmm.

150
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:48,408
Your mother-in-law's on the phone.

151
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:51,202
She's accidentally locked herself
in the garage again.

152
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:54,330
She said it's no rush,
but the stove is on.

153
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:59,460
[Mr. Shapiro] Good morning, students.

154
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:01,212
Who knows what this is?

155
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:03,798
That's a 34C, front clasp, demi-cup.

156
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:07,802
No, Trent. This is oppression.

157
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,271
Uh, they used to be made
of more flammable materials.

158
00:07:18,354 --> 00:07:19,188
The point is,

159
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:21,858
we are starting our unit
on the women's rights movement,

160
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:24,610
and it will take us all the way
till the end of the year.

161
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:27,905
We're studying the women's rights movement
for the next four months?

162
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:29,073
What about Watergate?

163
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:31,492
What about Iran-Contra? What about 9/11?

164
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:34,287
Uh, would you like to tell
the women in this classroom

165
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:36,581
that those events mean more to you
than their rights?

166
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:38,374
We need to know other things
for the AP test.

167
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,709
Reclaiming my time.

168
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:43,004
The first assignment.

169
00:07:43,087 --> 00:07:45,256
I need all of you to break up into groups

170
00:07:45,339 --> 00:07:48,217
and rewrite the Bill of Rights
as if it were written,

171
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:49,844
not by Founding Fathers

172
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,139
but instead by Founding Mothers.

173
00:07:55,057 --> 00:07:58,019
Can you believe this?
This is why we need real textbooks.

174
00:07:58,102 --> 00:07:59,812
Well, according to you,
I don't read books.

175
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,314
So I guess I'm cool with it.

176
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:02,732
[students murmuring]

177
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,946
Excuse me, is this seat taken?

178
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:12,283
Yeah, actually.
My superhot boyfriend. Mm-hmm.

179
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,993
And he's a real psycho, so…

180
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:16,412
-Damn. The cute ones are always taken.
-[Devi] Mm-hmm.

181
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:17,872
[chuckles]

182
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,540
How's your Valentine's Day going?

183
00:08:19,624 --> 00:08:21,167
It was good at the start,

184
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,711
and then I got Eric
on the compatibility quiz.

185
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:25,046
Mm. He's not so bad.

186
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:27,298
He's always the first to notice
when I get a new haircut.

187
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:28,216
I guess.

188
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,219
I just kind of wanted
to get my smokeshow boyfriend,

189
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:34,347
but apparently the computer feels
like he's out of my league.

190
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:37,183
Okay. First of all,
you're my smokeshow girlfriend.

191
00:08:37,266 --> 00:08:39,268
And secondly,

192
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:42,146
the computer thinks
you're exactly in my league.

193
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,356
[McEnroe] Hallelujah.

194
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,484
Who cares if Devi's perfect match was Eric

195
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:49,320
as long as Paxton's perfect match was her?

196
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,447
According to Nobel scientists,

197
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:54,575
she was basically the only one
in the whole world for him.

198
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,285
So suck on that, Haley.

199
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:57,995
-[fire whooshes]
-[yelps]

200
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,957
Oh, it seems as if it is still flammable.
Everyone out!

201
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,917
Men and teachers last.

202
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,418
[students murmuring]

203
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:14,053
Yo, babe. [exhales]
I have an amazing Valentine's plan.

204
00:09:14,762 --> 00:09:16,931
Picture this, candlelight dinner.

205
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:19,183
You, me, my Uncle Joe.

206
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,560
Wear something sexy.

207
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:24,313
Yeah. Um, Trent, I think we should talk.

208
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:25,565
Oh wow.

209
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,150
Anytime someone says that to me,

210
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,611
it always means great news.

211
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:31,529
Uh-huh. Yeah.

212
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:35,074
Well, I don't think I can come
to Valentine's with your Uncle Joe.

213
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:37,785
Why? Is it because
he hogs the crescent rolls?

214
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:41,622
Or are you worried he's gonna try
to put you in one of his TV commercials?

215
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:44,917
One of his, 'scuse me, whats?

216
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,587
His commercials.
He owns a chain of blinds stores.

217
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,006
Chances are you've seen them
while pumping gas.

218
00:09:50,089 --> 00:09:53,676
Wait. Is your Uncle Joe Captain Joe,

219
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,970
the pirate who makes high prices
walk the plank?

220
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:58,806
That's him. Yeah,
whenever we have dinner together,

221
00:09:58,889 --> 00:10:01,642
he always ropes everyone at the table
into being in his next commercial.

222
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:03,728
Oh, wow.

223
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:06,314
But we could always
just go out to a restaurant.

224
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:07,481
No, I'll be there.

225
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:12,069
Valentine's Day is about family.
Thanks for reminding me of that.

226
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,446
[both chuckle]

227
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:17,366
[Ben] Hey.

228
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,870
Something wrong?
You kinda bit my head off back there.

229
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:23,956
Yeah. Well, I didn't love
the way you talked to me earlier.

230
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,459
That little library card remark
was messed up.

231
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:29,337
Aneesa, I was just teasing.
It was just a joke.

232
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:32,757
Was it a joke?
You seem genuinely embarrassed by me.

233
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,800
Of course, I'm not embarrassed of you.

234
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:38,471
You're amazing,
and pretty, and cool, and fun.

235
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:41,098
So what if you don't know
who some dumb author is.

236
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,267
I don't expect you
to know everything that I know.

237
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:44,935
There it is. Right there.

238
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,437
You're so condescending.

239
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,772
[inhales deeply] You know what?

240
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:50,358
Hmm. Think I'm gonna take
a rain check on Valentine's dinner.

241
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,901
What? Aneesa, wait.

242
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:53,986
Oh, come on. I didn't mean it like that.

243
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:55,780
[sighs]

244
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:57,448
-[door closes]
-[faucet running]

245
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,371
[smacks lips]

246
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,706
Here we are again
in the old bathroom. [chuckles]

247
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:09,043
Yeah. Um, Fabiola, about that.

248
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:12,505
I'm really sorry I kissed you.

249
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:15,925
Can we just forget about it?

250
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:17,885
Yeah. Yeah, no problem.

251
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:20,388
I'm… I'm still getting over Eve, so…

252
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:22,431
consider it forgotten.

253
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:24,517
Thank you.

254
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:29,730
Good talk.

255
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:35,736
-[somber music playing]
-[door opens, closes]

256
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:42,326
Whoa! Is that homemade rigatones with…
[imitating Italian accent] …mozzarella?

257
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,454
Yep, as long as you count
microwaving a Stouffer's as homemade.

258
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,457
I did cut that sprig of parsley
and put it on there.

259
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:50,668
[clicks tongue] Uh, I think that's mint.

260
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,087
Nice, refreshing. [chuckles]

261
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:54,046
[Devi] Hmm.

262
00:11:56,757 --> 00:12:00,469
Look at us. You know, at first glance,
we probably seem like a real odd couple.

263
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:03,431
Because, you know,
you're Paxton Hall-Yoshida.

264
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:06,100
And I'm just, ugh,
nerdy little me with no abs.

265
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:08,686
What? Don't talk about yourself like that.

266
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:11,564
Come on, you're awesome.
You're beautiful. You're smart.

267
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:13,023
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I'm just saying,

268
00:12:13,107 --> 00:12:16,235
despite that, those MIT scientists
know what they're talking about.

269
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:20,406
-We're really good together.
-Totes. Just like marinara and mint.

270
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:24,869
Sure, or things that more classically
go together. [chuckles]

271
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:26,996
But anyway, we're a good team.

272
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:29,623
-Yeah, we are a good team.
-Mm-hmm.

273
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:30,708
Hey, speaking of teams,

274
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:33,377
I'm gonna play paintball tomorrow
with a bunch of dudes. Wanna come?

275
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:35,129
I absolutely do not.

276
00:12:35,212 --> 00:12:37,548
But yet again,
I love that we like different things,

277
00:12:37,631 --> 00:12:39,842
because per the computer,
opposites attract.

278
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:40,968
They sure do.

279
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:43,721
Happy Valentine's Day, Devi.

280
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:48,017
Oh, shit.

281
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,644
I totally forgot.
I bought fancy Parm for this.

282
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:53,230
Not even the green can.
It's like a little brick I have to grate.

283
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,232
So, BRB. [chuckles]

284
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:58,027
[McEnroe] Devi was finally at peace
in her relationship.

285
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:59,820
And though the bar was low,

286
00:12:59,904 --> 00:13:02,573
she was having
the most romantic meal of her life.

287
00:13:02,656 --> 00:13:05,034
All she had to do now was lean back

288
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:07,703
and wait for her chiseled,
doting boyfriend

289
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,331
to bring her freshly grated cheese and…

290
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:13,834
lie to her frickin' face.

291
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:16,003
-What the hell?
-[sighs]

292
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:20,090
Cheers to my most romantic
Valentine's Day dinner yet.

293
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:22,885
-Eye contact.
-Mmm. Sure.

294
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:25,596
Eye contact. Eleanor, eye contact.

295
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:27,014
Yep. [chuckles]

296
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:32,645
So, Captain Joe.

297
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:34,230
You know, I'm a big fan.

298
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:38,609
I love the commercial
where you slash prices and some blinds

299
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:40,027
with your hook hand.

300
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:42,404
Thanks. Actually, I didn't mean
to rip those blinds in half,

301
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:44,406
but we forgot to roll sound
on the other take, so…

302
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,742
The performances are phenomenal.

303
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:48,536
Where do you find the actors?

304
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:50,955
Mmm… Mostly family dinners.

305
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:53,666
Oh, hey, you know, Eleanor is an actor.

306
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:55,417
-[chuckles]
-A really good one.

307
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:58,712
Well, if you want,
you can play a salty sea wench.

308
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:00,840
In your next commercial?

309
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:02,424
Yeah, sure.

310
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:04,802
[inspirational music playing]

311
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:05,886
Oh my God.

312
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:08,681
I'm a working actor.

313
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:12,226
I'm a working actor. Thank you so much.

314
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:15,187
Yeah, anything for someone
who makes my nephew here so happy.

315
00:14:16,063 --> 00:14:18,315
Oh, not even weed makes me this happy.

316
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,110
-[sighs]
-[chuckles sheepishly]

317
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:27,032
Happy Valentine's Day, sweetheart.

318
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:30,786
[sighs]

319
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:36,292
[door opens]

320
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:40,087
Oh, Devi. Hi. Hey, do you want
to have a little bit of dinner with me?

321
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:42,756
Your grandmother's having Galentine's
with one of her cliques,

322
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,843
and believe I saw your cousin sneak
into your teacher's crappy little Honda.

323
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:48,512
Uh, no, thanks. I already ate.
I'm just gonna go up to my room.

324
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,348
Uh, I have a big test tomorrow.

325
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,310
[McEnroe] As Nalini envisioned her night

326
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:57,897
watching a Hallmark movie
with an inanimate object,

327
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,482
she started to entertain the possibility

328
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,611
that she might need
to broaden her social horizons.

329
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:06,614
[Nalini] Hi, Rhyah! Still free tomorrow?

330
00:15:07,197 --> 00:15:08,908
This is Nalini Vishwakumar.

331
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:11,660
[McEnroe] Devi hadn't mentioned the card
to Paxton,

332
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:15,080
instead she had spent
the rest of dinner pretending to be happy,

333
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:18,334
like I did when I got runner-up
at Wimbledon in 1980.

334
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,711
Not doing a great job there, bud.

335
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:23,589
Wow, you really weren't lying

336
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:24,882
about the Parmesan.

337
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,425
-It's delicious.
-I know, right?

338
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:27,718
Yeah. Uh-huh.

339
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:31,805
I sure can trust you
when it comes to cheese.

340
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,102
[sighs]

341
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:41,065
[McEnroe] But obviously
Devi was spiraling.

342
00:15:41,565 --> 00:15:43,484
Why did Paxton lie to her?

343
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:44,735
And, more importantly,

344
00:15:44,818 --> 00:15:47,571
was his perfect match
who she thought it was?

345
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:48,739
[sighs]

346
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,075
[upbeat music playing]

347
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:57,081
Eric, we need to talk about
the compatibility quiz. I know you got me.

348
00:15:57,164 --> 00:16:01,460
Shh! Keep it down.
You trying to ruin my rep, dork?

349
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:03,045
Excuse me, nerd?

350
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:08,050
I've spent the last two years
trying to date someone who's hot

351
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:09,426
and become popular,

352
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:12,805
so that I'm not just the kid
who lost his dad…

353
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:15,474
[McEnroe] Damn. Maybe they were alike.

354
00:16:15,557 --> 00:16:16,600
…at Disneyland.

355
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,727
I had to wait for him
near the security desk.

356
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:19,853
Oh my God.

357
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:21,814
[McEnroe] Ugh. This kid.

358
00:16:21,897 --> 00:16:25,567
Well, I know Paxton made you trade cards
with him. So tell me who he got.

359
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:29,446
-Hmm. Interesting. What's it worth to ya?
-Just give me the card, Eric.

360
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:31,782
Oh, you mean this card?

361
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:36,286
Well, it is gonna cost you big time.

362
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:38,247
Haley.

363
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:39,623
Damn it.

364
00:16:39,707 --> 00:16:42,668
No, I don't. No! I never said that.

365
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:45,421
-Is she laughing? That's five bucks then.
-[Haley] I'm not laughing.

366
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:46,839
[scoffs]

367
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:51,260
How'd the rest of your Valentine's go?
Did you break up with--

368
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:53,137
Ah! My boyfriend.

369
00:16:55,764 --> 00:16:57,808
I'm gonna take that as a no.

370
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:02,938
No, I didn't break up with him.
Instead, I used him to get to his uncle.

371
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,149
I'm gonna need you to elaborate on that.

372
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:07,443
His uncle's Captain Joe.

373
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:08,694
The blinds guy?

374
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:11,780
Yep, and I weaseled my way
into one of his commercials.

375
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,700
Oh my God, Eleanor,
you're gonna be in a commercial?

376
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:16,910
Yeah, but I feel really gross about it.

377
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:18,704
So what are you gonna do?

378
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:22,207
I think I have
to let both Trent and the commercial go.

379
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:26,545
Maybe one of these days
I'll meet someone who's right for me,

380
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:28,756
whose uncle also makes commercials.

381
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:34,970
And so Eric shows me Paxton's card,
and it's frigging Haley.

382
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:38,599
Are you worried that something
is going on between them?

383
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,309
I don't know.

384
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:41,518
I don't think so.

385
00:17:42,102 --> 00:17:44,104
It's just… Why else would he lie?

386
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:48,025
Well, it was wrong for Paxton
to be dishonest.

387
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:50,069
But why do you care so much
about this test?

388
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:50,986
It's just…

389
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:56,366
when I see him talking to Haley,
I feel really jealous.

390
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,994
They look so good together.

391
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:02,414
Like, no one would bat an eye
if you said that they were a couple.

392
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,667
And you think you and Paxton
are getting tons of eye bats?

393
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:08,504
I can't help but worry
that this is some weird phase for him

394
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:10,964
where he dates a quirky, smart girl.

395
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:13,008
And at any moment, he's gonna be like,

396
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:15,177
"Yo, you know what I miss?"

397
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:19,556
"Superhot models with six-pack abs
and, like, symmetrical boobs."

398
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:20,849
[laughs]

399
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:24,394
First of all, girl,
nobody has symmetrical boobs.

400
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:26,647
Everybody's got a Biggie and a Smalls.

401
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:30,526
And secondly, that way of thinking
is selling you both short.

402
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:32,653
-Like, look at this girl.
-Do I have to?

403
00:18:32,736 --> 00:18:34,571
[Devi] Yes. Look at her stories.

404
00:18:35,155 --> 00:18:38,200
Here she is doing
a cool dance, ironically. [scoffs]

405
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:41,370
And here she is doing Pilates.
Probably without even queefing.

406
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:44,832
-And here she is playing paintball.
-[Haley laughing]

407
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:49,211
Wait, she's playing paintball?
Doc, I gotta go.

408
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,380
Devi, don't. Let's work through this.

409
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:53,132
Devi, don't go--

410
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,424
[sighs]

411
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:55,884
Shit.

412
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:58,804
[mouth full] Mmm, an açaí bowl.
I never had one of these before.

413
00:18:58,887 --> 00:18:59,930
-Really?
-[Nalini] Mm-mm.

414
00:19:00,013 --> 00:19:01,598
Oh, açaí bowls are great.

415
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:04,893
They're loaded with antioxidants, fiber.
They boost brain function.

416
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:08,772
But really, they're just a way to eat tons
of sugar and pretend it's healthy for you.

417
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,399
-[Nalini chuckles]
-[Rhyah laughs]

418
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:13,110
You sound like my husband.
He had a huge sweet tooth.

419
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:14,778
One time he had three Pizookies.

420
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:16,613
That's a cookie the size of a pie.

421
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,407
Got very sick to the stomach.

422
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:22,661
But even in severe abdominal pain,
he was still able to make me laugh.

423
00:19:22,744 --> 00:19:23,871
[chuckles]

424
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:26,498
I'm sorry, Nalini.
Must be really difficult without him.

425
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,210
Yesterday was harder
than I expected, you know.

426
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:34,047
I always thought Valentine's Day
was stupid, but last night…

427
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:35,007
[inhales deeply]

428
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:37,426
…I would've given anything for him
to walk through the door

429
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:39,469
with a $5 teddy bear from the gas station.

430
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,305
I wish you could've had that too.

431
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:46,476
Saw a picture of him in your office.
Good for you, girl.

432
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:48,645
[both laugh]

433
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:51,190
-He was nice to look at, wasn't he?
-[Rhyah] Mmm.

434
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,775
But that's not what I miss most about him.

435
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:56,862
I truly just miss having
my best friend around.

436
00:19:57,738 --> 00:20:00,490
Well, it sounds like a new friend
is just what's needed.

437
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:06,205
Let's do something fun.
Have you ever had a blowout?

438
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:08,540
I fear this açaí bowl may lead to one.

439
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,792
[laughs]

440
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:14,630
No. No, no. I meant your hair.
There's a blow-dry bar over there.

441
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:16,757
-No, please. [chuckles]
-[Rhyah laughs]

442
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:19,551
-I'm so embarrassed.
-[laughs]

443
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:20,594
Sounds like fun.

444
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,475
What up? Let's get our P-ball on.

445
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:28,852
Hey, I didn't think you wanted to play.

446
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:30,103
I changed my mind.

447
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:31,730
As I always say,

448
00:20:31,813 --> 00:20:33,982
a couple that shoots guns together
has funs together--

449
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,067
-[paintball gun fires]
-Ah!

450
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:37,736
Wow, that is a sensitive trigger.

451
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:38,654
[chuckles] Dope.

452
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:41,823
Well, we already picked teams,
but Trent's team is down a person.

453
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:46,495
Oh. Yeah. Sure. I'll be on Trent's team.

454
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:48,455
All right, cool. Let's go!

455
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:52,709
Welcome to the squad, Crazy Devi.

456
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:55,921
Okay, I've given it some thought,
and here's our strategy.

457
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:58,507
If you see someone on the other team,
shoot paintballs at them,

458
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,467
and then the second part
of that strategy is

459
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:03,470
don't let them shoot paintballs
that hit you.

460
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:06,348
Oh, and be careful
'cause Haley's a sick shot.

461
00:21:06,431 --> 00:21:08,308
[scoffs] How good could she be?

462
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:14,273
-Jesus.
-Yeah, she and Paxton are gonna smoke us.

463
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,775
Oh, which reminds me.
I'm gonna get high before we do this.

464
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:18,652
[McEnroe] As Devi looked over

465
00:21:18,735 --> 00:21:21,989
at the so-called perfect match
of Haley and Paxton,

466
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:26,535
she realized she had let this dumb
compatibility test mess with her head,

467
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:30,247
and the only way to go forward
was to let the test go.

468
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:34,084
But also, she decided the only way
she could let the test go

469
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:36,795
is if she kicked Haley's ass at paintball

470
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:39,840
proving that she was
Paxton's true perfect match.

471
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:43,343
What? You thought
she was gonna be mature about this?

472
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:46,054
-["Not About You" by Haiku Hands playing]
-[paintball guns firing]

473
00:21:46,638 --> 00:21:47,889
♪ It's not about you ♪

474
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:50,809
♪ All talk, hold court
Oh Lord, I understood… ♪

475
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:52,436
[groans]

476
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:56,648
[gasps] Wow. Am I amazing at this?

477
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:57,774
[paintball gun firing]

478
00:21:57,858 --> 00:21:59,234
♪ Shut up ♪

479
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,069
♪ It's not about me either… ♪

480
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:02,529
-[paintball gun firing]
-Ow.

481
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,239
♪ Chill ♪

482
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,616
♪ It's not about you, shut up ♪

483
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,702
♪ It's not about me either ♪

484
00:22:08,785 --> 00:22:10,287
♪ It's us versus the grim reaper… ♪

485
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:11,621
-[paintball gun firing]
-[groans]

486
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:14,624
Oh, I bruise so easily. [exhales]

487
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:16,960
♪ I'm gonna ♪

488
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:18,795
♪ I'm gonna ♪

489
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:20,964
♪ It's not about you ♪

490
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:22,758
♪ I'ma kick your arse ♪

491
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:24,676
♪ I'ma kick your arse ♪

492
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,053
♪ I'ma kick your arse ♪

493
00:22:26,136 --> 00:22:29,181
♪ If you don't drop the facade
I said I'll hit the mark on the head ♪

494
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:30,974
♪ I said
I'll bring you back from the dead ♪

495
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,893
♪ I did all that while you were in bed ♪

496
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:34,770
♪ And still had time
To set the next trend ♪

497
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:35,729
♪ It's not about you ♪

498
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:40,108
-On your knees.
-What?

499
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:44,029
Bet you thought you could beat me, huh?

500
00:22:44,613 --> 00:22:47,240
I might not be as cute as you
or as limber as you,

501
00:22:47,324 --> 00:22:49,451
and my hair might not be
as shiny as yours,

502
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:52,412
but I do have determination and grit

503
00:22:52,496 --> 00:22:54,456
like the noble cockroach.

504
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,208
I don't know what's happening.

505
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:58,877
But could you shoot me so I can be out
of the game and get a soda?

506
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,797
Okay, I'm gonna shoot you
when I'm good and ready to-- [groans]

507
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,882
[paintball gun firing]

508
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:07,135
-Yes! Blue team wins. Let's go!
-[Haley] Whoo!

509
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:09,429
-Whoo!
-[laughs, claps]

510
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:10,347
Yeah!

511
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:16,937
Aneesa. Neese, wait.
You have to talk to me.

512
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:21,024
I know that I messed up,
and I was a dick. I'm really sorry.

513
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:23,819
Yeah, I don't think this is working out.

514
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,239
What? No. Why?

515
00:23:27,322 --> 00:23:29,157
I don't think you respect me.

516
00:23:29,908 --> 00:23:31,701
And you make me feel stupid,

517
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:33,245
and I'm not stupid.

518
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:37,207
I deserve someone who's excited
to be with me just as I am

519
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:40,794
and who doesn't wish I was someone else.

520
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:43,505
[somber music playing]

521
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:52,264
Shit. Why are you in every room I enter?

522
00:23:52,973 --> 00:23:56,143
I don't know the answer to that.
Um, I can go, though.

523
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,520
[sniffling]

524
00:23:59,479 --> 00:24:01,940
-[sobbing softly]
-Wait. Are you okay?

525
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:05,026
[sighs]

526
00:24:07,237 --> 00:24:08,488
Ben and I just broke up.

527
00:24:09,156 --> 00:24:09,990
Oh.

528
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:13,118
I-- I'm really sorry, Aneesa.

529
00:24:13,201 --> 00:24:17,205
[sighs] It was for the best.
He wasn't really right for me.

530
00:24:18,248 --> 00:24:19,875
So I guess the test was wrong for you.

531
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:22,210
[chuckles] No. No.
I lied about getting Ben.

532
00:24:24,171 --> 00:24:27,257
-I actually got a random freshman.
-[chuckles]

533
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:28,175
[chuckles]

534
00:24:29,259 --> 00:24:33,555
Listen, I am sure
you will find another great guy soon.

535
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:41,688
Or, you know, a great girl
if kissing me wasn't a fluke.

536
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:46,151
I'm sure the right person is out there.

537
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,068
[chuckles gently]

538
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:50,113
[McEnroe] Even though the conversation
had some mixed signals,

539
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:52,741
Fabiola felt good about it.
It was a start.

540
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:56,328
Well, in the meantime,
I'm here if you want to talk.

541
00:24:57,787 --> 00:24:58,747
Thanks, Fabiola.

542
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:02,042
You're a good friend.

543
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,176
[boy] Watch it, dude.

544
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:20,352
[Paxton] Nice job, Haley.

545
00:25:20,435 --> 00:25:21,770
I can't believe you shot me.

546
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:24,814
You saw Haley and I sitting there,
and you shot me, and I'm your girlfriend.

547
00:25:24,898 --> 00:25:25,982
She was on my team.

548
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:27,442
And I thought we were a team.

549
00:25:28,109 --> 00:25:30,654
-What is going on with you?
-I know you lied.

550
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:33,615
I know you got Haley on the test,
and you lied to me. Why?

551
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:35,575
I don't know. Maybe because

552
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:37,869
I thought you might take it badly
if you knew I got Haley.

553
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:39,371
Why would you think that?

554
00:25:39,454 --> 00:25:41,957
Well, because of how you're acting
right now.

555
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:46,044
And also you've been really weird
since Haley and I became friends again,

556
00:25:46,127 --> 00:25:48,380
even though you're the one
who made me apologize.

557
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:51,466
Sorry, but she's so beautiful
and good with guns,

558
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:55,220
and could be Lara Croft for Halloween.
How am I supposed to compete with that?

559
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:56,388
You don't.

560
00:25:56,471 --> 00:25:58,848
Haley and I are just friends.
I'm with you.

561
00:25:58,932 --> 00:26:02,686
I know, but I don't understand why.

562
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:03,645
Why what?

563
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:06,940
Why I'm with you? Because I like you.

564
00:26:07,023 --> 00:26:11,486
Yeah, but why?
No one else thinks we make any sense.

565
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:14,573
No, you don't think we make any sense.

566
00:26:14,656 --> 00:26:16,950
[sighs] Because when we walk
down the halls,

567
00:26:17,033 --> 00:26:18,743
I know what everyone's thinking.

568
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:21,413
"Oh, why is he with her?
He's too good for her."

569
00:26:21,496 --> 00:26:23,999
Who cares what people think?

570
00:26:24,082 --> 00:26:26,084
I think you're good enough for me.

571
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:28,587
But I can't keep trying
to convince you of that.

572
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,339
What does that mean?

573
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,426
Look, Devi, I-I really like you, but…

574
00:26:36,261 --> 00:26:38,638
I-I don't think
we can have a real relationship

575
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:40,223
until you like yourself.

576
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:43,226
[somber song playing]

577
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:44,185
I'm sorry.

578
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:48,106
♪ I'll burn down ♪

579
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:57,657
♪ And sleep in the warm ashes
On the ground ♪

580
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:00,368
Whoa, Eleanor!

581
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:03,830
Are you here to play paintball too?

582
00:27:03,913 --> 00:27:06,291
Weird. I wouldn't have pegged that
as one of your interests.

583
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:08,918
It's not, Trent. I wanted to talk to you.

584
00:27:09,002 --> 00:27:11,796
-Well, then it's good I was here also.
-Uh-huh.

585
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:15,175
Let me just dive in. There's something
I have to confess to you.

586
00:27:15,842 --> 00:27:18,637
I used you
to get into your uncle's commercial.

587
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:21,473
I was gonna break up with you,
and then you told me about it,

588
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:25,769
and I deployed my incredible acting skills
to manipulate you.

589
00:27:26,269 --> 00:27:30,190
But I won't take the commercial,
and you'll never have to see me again.

590
00:27:30,273 --> 00:27:31,900
We have a lot of classes together.

591
00:27:32,484 --> 00:27:35,320
Okay, well, yeah, you'll see me in those.

592
00:27:35,403 --> 00:27:37,405
But I can wear my veil if that would help.

593
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:39,282
Eleanor, I knew you were gonna dump me.

594
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:41,117
I'm not a great boyfriend.

595
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:44,329
I've been told by many guidance counselors
that I'm clinically immature.

596
00:27:45,747 --> 00:27:48,750
-I actually manipulated you.
-What?

597
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,502
I dangled Uncle Joe in front of you

598
00:27:50,585 --> 00:27:53,755
like a carrot in front of a person
who really likes carrots.

599
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:56,466
I knew his Hollywood connections
would make you stay with me.

600
00:27:56,549 --> 00:28:00,679
Wait, so we deceived each other
to get what we wanted?

601
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:04,516
Oh my God.
We're like a real celebrity couple.

602
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:05,475
[chuckles]

603
00:28:06,434 --> 00:28:07,352
[sighs]

604
00:28:07,977 --> 00:28:09,646
I really like you, Eleanor.

605
00:28:10,313 --> 00:28:13,775
I know it seems like I'm knee-deep
in tang twenty-four-sevskies, but…

606
00:28:14,984 --> 00:28:18,446
you're actually my first girlfriend,
and I'm a little insecure about that.

607
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:20,532
[redeeming music playing]

608
00:28:27,747 --> 00:28:29,249
Devi. Guess what?

609
00:28:29,332 --> 00:28:31,292
I did a gal pal hang today.

610
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:34,713
Please check out my blowout.
I look like a newswoman.

611
00:28:36,005 --> 00:28:37,257
Yeah. That… That's great, Mom.

612
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:38,550
Is everything okay?

613
00:28:38,633 --> 00:28:42,846
Y-Yeah. Um, I just didn't do well
on that test I told you about earlier.

614
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:44,723
[stomping foot]

615
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:47,684
Devi.

616
00:28:49,185 --> 00:28:50,729
What actually happened?

617
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:52,480
Is this about a boy?

618
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:55,483
Even though I won't let you date,
I do care if you're heartbroken.

619
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:56,401
[sniffling]

620
00:28:57,193 --> 00:28:59,821
Yeah. It's about a boy.

621
00:28:59,904 --> 00:29:02,449
And I really, really liked him.

622
00:29:06,828 --> 00:29:07,829
Come here.

623
00:29:09,539 --> 00:29:10,915
[sobbing]

624
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:14,085
["Before the Fall" by Afternoon Bike Ride
and Ryan Hemsworth]

625
00:29:17,797 --> 00:29:18,798
[sniffling]

626
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:23,762
♪ Once upon a time
A songbird flew away for good ♪

627
00:29:24,512 --> 00:29:28,725
♪ Every melody went unheard
In a concrete world ♪

628
00:29:28,808 --> 00:29:33,396
♪ Now her joyful hum
Echoes through trees ♪

629
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:38,151
♪ That used to grow
Where they've paved in the street ♪

630
00:29:39,861 --> 00:29:44,783
♪ Winter's cloak covered
The tracks of the tyrants ♪

631
00:29:49,871 --> 00:29:55,168
♪ Spring couldn't bring on
The promise of June ♪

632
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:05,804
♪ With no voice to sing
And nothing to bloom ♪
